Hobak Saengchae (cold zucchini salad)
  --Cesar Perez

Dressing:
2 tbsp shoyu
1 tbsp rice vinegar
1 tbsp gochugaru
1 tbsp chili crisp
1 tbsp toasted sesame oil
1 tsp granulated sugar
1 garlic clove, minced

Whisk together all the ingredients until the sugar is dissolved.
2 medium zucchini, shaved into thin ribbons
1/2 cucumber, thinly sliced
1/4 red onion, thinly sliced, soaked in ice water
2 green onions, thinly sliced, soaked in ice water
1 tbsp toasted sesame seeds

In a large bowl, combine the shaved zucchini, cucumber, red onion, and green onions. Pour the dressing over the vegetables and toss gently to combine. Let sit in the refrigerator for at least 30 min to an hour before serving. Garnish with toasted sesame seeds and serve. 


